ordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/android-phone-charging.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/android-phone-charging.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e Almost all Android smartphones today support fast charging, but expecting any fast charger to work the same way isn\u0026#39;t accurate. Most Android OEMs use \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/fast-chargers-vs-regular-chargers-differences/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003edifferent fast charging protocols\u003c/a\u003e, which means the charger you\u0026#39;re using might not work as expected. There are many fast charging protocols like USB-PD, PPS, or proprietary ones like SuperVOOC used by OnePlus.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eUsing the right charger will charge your phone as intended, and while an incompatible fast charger won\u0026#39;t damage your phone\u0026#39;s port, it likely won\u0026#39;t deliver fast charging. So, \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/phone-charger-tips-to-select/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebefore buying a new charger\u003c/a\u003e, check your phone\u0026#39;s supported charging protocol to ensure compatibility — otherwise, you won\u0026#39;t get the speed you\u0026#39;re expecting.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"you-should-only-use-your-phone-brand-39-s-original-charger\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            You should only use your phone brand\u0026#39;s original charger\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"third-party-chargers-are-fine-if-they-meet-the-right-standards\"\u003e\n            Third-party chargers are fine if they meet the right standards\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n              